Miss World Africa 2017 Magline Jeruto has said she is working to establish a Sh60 million autism centre in Elgeyo Marakwet, the first one in Kenya. She spoke as she launched her campaign against stigmatisation of children with autism. Jeruto was voted fifth in a beauty pageant in Sanya, China, in 2017 and later crowned Miss World Africa. She is working with partners and said she will wants a sustainable campaign. She asked parents of children with autism to take them for assessment in special schools instead of hiding them at home.